Lebanese Prime Minister Omar Karami announced resignation of his government on Monday amid massive demonstrations over the assassination of ex-prime minister Rafik al Hariri.
Advice from former speakers and prime ministers will be taken into consideration.
Out of concern that the government does not become an obstacle to the good of the country, I announce the resignation of the government I had the honour to lead, Karami told parliament in Beirut.
Lebanon plunged into political turbulence after Hariri's killing, for which the opposition has blamed pro-Syrian authorities.
